ction of Sacred Harp Music (AFC 1943/004)", "url": "https://lccn.loc.gov/2006700229"}], "repository": "american folklife center", "rights": "Restrictions may apply.", "source_collection": "Amazing Grace", "subjects": ["Hymns", "shape note singing", "sound recording"], "title": "Speech by Paine Denson, excerpt from a field recording, \"Speeches about The Sacred Harp"}, "language": ["english"], "mime_type": ["audio/mpeg"], "number": ["http://www.loc.gov/resource/ihas.200049058.0"], "number_former_id": ["http://www.loc.gov/resource/ihas.200049058.0"], "online_format": ["audio"], "original_format": ["sound recording"], "partof": ["american folklife center", "amazing grace", "the library of congress celebrates the songs of america"], "resources": [{"audio": "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/public/afc/afcihas-200049058/200049058.mp3", "files": 1, "paprika_resource_path": "/sets/afc/afcihas-200049058", "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/afc.afcihas-200049058/"}], "shelf_id": "AFS 06714 A", "subject": ["hymns", "shape note singing", "sound recording"], "timestamp": "2024-09-28T06:19:18.844Z", "title": "Speech by Paine Denson, excerpt from a field recording, \"Speeches about The Sacred Harp", "type": ["sound recording"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/ihas.200049058/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["https://hdl.loc.gov/loc.afc/ihas.200049060", "http://www.loc.gov/resource/afc.afcihas-200049060/", "http://www.loc.gov/item/ihas.200049060/"], "campaigns": [], "contributor": ["mayo, seymour"], "date": "1946", "dates": ["1946"], "description": [""], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2024-09-28T06:17:59.803Z", "group": ["paprika-afc"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/ihas.200049060/", "image_url": [], "index": 8, "item": {"call_number": ["AFS 08527 A"], "contributors": ["Mayo, Seymour (Singer)"], "date": "1946", "digital_id": ["https://hdl.loc.gov/loc.afc/ihas.200049060"], "format": "sound recording", "genre": ["sound recording"], "language": "eng", "medium": ["1 sound disc : anaolog, mono."], "notes": ["Date: Recorded by Margot Mayo, Stu Jamieson and Freyda Simon in 1946", "Venue: Recorded in Allen, KY"], "related_items": [{"title": "Margot Mayo Collection (AFC 1948/023)", "url": "https://lccn.loc.gov/2008700402"}], "repository": "american folklife center", "rights": "Restrictions may apply.", "source_collection": "Amazing Grace", "subjects": ["sound recording"], "title": "Amazing grace"}, "language": ["english"], "mime_type": ["audio/mpeg"], "number": ["http://www.loc.gov/resource/ihas.200049060.0"], "number_former_id": ["http://www.loc.gov/resource/ihas.200049060.0"], "online_format": ["audio"], "original_format": ["sound recording"], "partof": ["american folklife center", "amazing grace", "the library of congress celebrates the songs of america"], "resources": [{"audio": "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/public/afc/afcihas-200049060/200049060.mp3", "files": 1, "paprika_resource_path": "/sets/afc/afcihas-200049060", "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/afc.afcihas-200049060/"}], "shelf_id": "AFS 08527 A", "subject": ["sound recording"], "timestamp": "2024-09-28T06:19:18.844Z", "title": "Amazing grace", "type": ["sound recording"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/ihas.200049060/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://lccn.loc.gov/2024618001", "http://www.loc.gov/item/2024618001/", "https://hdl.loc.gov/loc.gdc/gdcdatasets.2024618001", "http://www.loc.gov/resource/gdcdatasets.2024618001/"], "campaigns": [], "contributor": ["chasanoff, allan", "library of congress", "elozua, raymon"], "date": "2024", "dates": ["2024"], "description": ["Collection compiled by Allan Chasanoff and Raymon Elozua. The collection highlights the history of the hymn \u201cAmazing Grace\u201d from the earliest printing of the song to selected performances of it on published and field recordings. These items have been collected from several divisions in the Library of Congress, including the Music Division, the American Folklife Center, the Motion Picture, Broadcasting and Recorded Sound Division, and the Rare Books Division. Also available here is the Chasanoff/Elozua Amazing Grace Collection of data on published recorded performances of the hymn \"Amazing Grace\" by more than 3000 different musicians or ensembles. The recordings in the Chasanoff/Elozua \"Amazing Grace\" Collection were made between the 1930s and 2000. The audio formats represented in the collection include: compact disc, mp3 files (all acquired legally), vinyl long-playing 33-1/3 rpm discs, 78 rpm discs, cassette tapes, and various video media. The full breadth of the collection is revealed by the great range of performance styles: big band, blues, classical, country, 'easy listening,' electronic, folk, gospel, different styles of jazz, 'novelty,' operatic, pop, rap, rock, rhythm 'n' blues, soul, and various ethnic, or 'world music,' styles. The wide array of performers include children's groups, religious ensembles, concert bands, bagpipers, steel guitarists, and American Indians. Title from MusRef entry ; viewed October 17, 2024 Additional title from original database ; viewed October 17, 2024 Notes/description from original database ; viewed October 17, 2024"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2024-11-17T07:05:46.128Z", "group": ["catalog-split-08", "catalog", "gdcdatasets", "main-catalog-split-08", "general-collections-datasets"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2024618001/", "image_url": [], "index": 9, "item": {"call_number": ["BV370"], "contributors": ["Elozua, Raymon, 1947- compiler of source material", "Chasanoff, Allan, compiler of source material", "Library of Congress, editor"], "created_published": ["Washington, D.C. : Library of Congress, 2024."], "date": "2024", "digital_id": ["https://hdl.loc.gov/loc.gdc/gdcdatasets.2024618001"], "format": ["software"], "genre": ["Data sets", "Discographies", "Library catalogs"], "language": ["eng"], "medium": ["1 online resource (datasets)"], "notes": ["Collection compiled by Allan Chasanoff and Raymon Elozua.", "The collection highlights the history of the hymn \u201cAmazing Grace\u201d from the earliest printing of the song to selected performances of it on published and field recordings. These items have been collected from several divisions in the Library of Congress, including the Music Division, the American Folklife Center, the Motion Picture, Broadcasting and Recorded Sound Division, and the Rare Books Division. Also available here is the Chasanoff/Elozua Amazing Grace Collection of data on published recorded performances of the hymn \"Amazing Grace\" by more than 3000 different musicians or ensembles.", "The recordings in the Chasanoff/Elozua \"Amazing Grace\" Collection were made between the 1930s and 2000.", "The audio formats represented in the collection include: compact disc, mp3 files (all acquired legally), vinyl long-playing 33-1/3 rpm discs, 78 rpm discs, cassette tapes, and various video media.", "The full breadth of the collection is revealed by the great range of performance styles: big band, blues, classical, country, 'easy listening,' electronic, folk, gospel, different styles of jazz, 'novelty,' operatic, pop, rap, rock, rhythm 'n' blues, soul, and various ethnic, or 'world music,' styles. The wide array of performers include children's groups, religious ensembles, concert bands, bagpipers, steel guitarists, and American Indians.", "Title from MusRef entry ; viewed October 17, 2024", "Additional title from original database ; viewed October 17, 2024", "Notes/description from original database ; viewed October 17, 2024"], "other_title": ["Amazing grace collection", "Chasanoff/Elozua Amazing grace collection"], "related_items": [{"title": "", "url": "https://www.loc.gov/collections/amazing-grace/about-this-collection/"}, {"title": "Web archive of Amazing grace", "url": "https://atom.lib.byu.edu/musref/10709/"}], "subjects": ["Amazing grace (Hymn)", "Hymns, English--Discography", "Spirituals--Discography"], "title": "Amazing grace : [dataset]"}, "language": ["english"], "mime_type": ["application/zip"], "number": ["2024-11-15t14:47:00", "online resource", "2024618001"], "number_carrier_type": ["online resource"], "number_lccn": ["2024618001"], "number_source_modified": ["2024-11-15t14:47:00"], "online_format": ["compressed data"], "original_format": ["software, e-resource"], "other_title": ["Amazing grace collection", "Chasanoff/Elozua Amazing grace collection"], "partof": ["selected datasets", "amazing grace", "motion picture, broadcasting & recorded sound division", "catalog"], "resources": [{"files": 1, "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/gdcdatasets.2024618001/"}], "shelf_id": "BV370", "site": ["catalog"], "subject": ["hymns, english", "data sets", "library catalogs", "amazing grace (hymn)", "spirituals", "discographies", "discography"], "timestamp": "2024-11-17T07:10:50.815Z", "title": "Amazing grace : [dataset]", "type": ["software"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2024618001/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://lccn.loc.gov/2006700069", "http://www.loc.gov/item/2006700069/", "https://hdl.loc.gov/loc.rbc/pre.79197", "http://www.loc.gov/resource/rbc0001.2006pre79197/"], "campaigns": [], "contributor": ["pre- imprint collection (library of congress)", "newton, john", "cowper, william"], "date": "1779", "dates": ["1779"], "description": ["Olney Hymns was compiled by John Newton, the author of \"Amazing Grace\" and rector of a parish in Olney, England, and William Cowper, a poet and close friend of Newton. The book contained the first printing of \"Amazing Grace,\" which is numbered \"Hymn 41\" and begins at the bottom of page 53. The profits from the hymnal went to the benefit of Olney's poor. Olney Hymns later was published in New York in 1790 and in Philadelphia in 1791. In his preface to the book, Newton argued that hymns should be simpler than poetry and should be accessible to common people: \"There is a stile and manner suited to the composition of hymns, which may be more successfully, or at least more easily attained by a versifier, than by a poet. They should be Hymns, not Odes, if designed for public worship, and for the use of plain people. Perspicuity, simplicity and ease, should be chiefly attended to; and the imagery and coloring of poetry, if admitted at all, should be indulged very sparingly and with great judgment.\" World Digital Library."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2024-01-27T15:02:45.539Z", "group": ["rbc/scd", "rare-book-scan-on-demand-new"], "hassegments": true, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2006700069/", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:rbc:rbc0001:2006:2006pre79197:0018/full/pct:25/0/default.jpg", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:rbc:rbc0001:2006:2006pre79197:0018/full/pct:25/0/default.jpg#h=485&w=307", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:rbc:rbc0001:2006:2006pre79197:0018/full/pct:50/0/default.jpg#h=970&w=614", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:rbc:rbc0001:2006:2006pre79197:0018/full/pct:100/0/default.jpg#h=1940&w=1228"], "index": 10, "item": {"call_number": ["BV370 .N4 1779"], "contents": ["Book I. On select texts of scripture.--Book II. On occassional subjects.--Book III. On the progress and changes of the spiritual life."], "contributors": ["Newton, John, 1725-1807", "Cowper, William, 1731-1800", "Pre-1801 Imprint Collection (Library of Congress)"], "created_published": ["London, Printed and sold by W. Oliver, 1779."], "date": "1779", "digital_id": ["http://hdl.loc.gov/loc.rbc/pre.79197"], "format": ["text"], "language": ["eng"], "medium": ["xxvii, [1], 427 p. : front. (ports.) ; 17 cm."], "notes": ["280 hymns by Newton, 68 by Cowper.--Cf. Dictionary of National Biography.", "Errata: p. [xxviii]; publisher's advertisement: p. [428].", "Preface signed: John Newton.", "Without music.", "ESTC T18634", "Also available in digital form on the Library of Congress Web site."], "subjects": ["Hymns, English--Texts--Early works to 1800"], "summary": ["Olney Hymns was compiled by John Newton, the author of \"Amazing Grace\" and rector of a parish in Olney, England, and William Cowper, a poet and close friend of Newton. The book contained the first printing of \"Amazing Grace,\" which is numbered \"Hymn 41\" and begins at the bottom of page 53. The profits from the hymnal went to the benefit of Olney's poor. Olney Hymns later was published in New York in 1790 and in Philadelphia in 1791. In his preface to the book, Newton argued that hymns should be simpler than poetry and should be accessible to common people: \"There is a stile and manner suited to the composition of hymns, which may be more successfully, or at least more easily attained by a versifier, than by a poet. They should be Hymns, not Odes, if designed for public worship, and for the use of plain people. Perspicuity, simplicity and ease, should be chiefly attended to; and the imagery and coloring of poetry, if admitted at all, should be indulged very sparingly and with great judgment.\" World Digital Library."], "title": "Olney hymns : in three books"}, "language": ["english"], "mime_type": ["application/pdf", "image/tiff", "image/jpeg", "image/jp2"], "number": ["2006700069", "2024-01-11t12:36:17"], "number_lccn": ["2006700069"], "number_source_modified": ["2024-01-11t12:36:17"], "online_format": ["pdf", "image"], "original_format": ["book"], "partof": ["amazing grace", "catalog", "music division", "rare book selections", "rare book and special collections division", "world digital library"], "resources": [{"caption": "Page view", "files": 475, "image": "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/service:rbc:rbc0001:2006:2006pre79197:0018/full/pct:25/0/default.jpg", "pdf": "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/rbc/rbc0001/2006/2006pre79197/2006pre79197.pdf", "representative_index": 17, "search": "https://www.loc.gov/collections/amazing-grace/?fa=segmentof:rbc0001.2006pre79197/&fo=json&st=gallery", "segments": 475, "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/rbc0001.2006pre79197/"}], "segments": [{"count": 475, "link": "https://www.loc.gov/collections/amazing-grace/?fa=segmentof:rbc0001.2006pre79197/&fo=json&st=gallery", "url": "https://www.loc.gov/resource/rbc0001.2006pre79197/"}], "shelf_id": "BV370 .N4 1779", "site": ["catalog"], "subject": ["texts", "hymns, english", "early works to 1800"], "timestamp": "2024-01-27T15:52:23.574Z", "title": "Olney hymns : in three books", "type": ["text"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2006700069/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/ihas.200049064/", "http://www.loc.gov/resource/navcc.ihas-200049064-image/", "https://hdl.loc.gov/loc.music/ihas.200049064", "http://www.loc.gov/resource/navcc.ihas-200049064/"], "campaigns": [], "contributor": ["smith, h. r.", "amazing rhythm aces", "burton, barry \"byrd\""], "date": "1975", "dates": ["1975"], "description": [""], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2025-09-18T07:53:19.256Z", "group": ["paprika-navcc"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/ihas.200049064/", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/public:navcc:ihas-200049064-image:ihas-200049064/full/pct:25.0/0/default.jpg", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/public:navcc:ihas-200049064-image:ihas-200049064/full/pct:25.0/0/default.jpg#h=278&w=278", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/public:navcc:ihas-200049064-image:ihas-200049064/full/pct:50.0/0/default.jpg#h=557&w=557", "https://tile.loc.gov/image-services/iiif/public:navcc:ihas-200049064-image:ihas-200049064/full/pct:100.0/0/default.jpg#h=1114&w=1114"], "index": 11, "item": {"call_number": ["LC Classification: ABC 12142"], "contributors": ["Amazing Rhythm Aces (Performer)", "Smith, H. R. (Composer)", "Burton, Barry \"Byrd\" (Producer)"], "created_published": ["ABC Records, New York, 1975"], "date": "1975", "digital_id": ["https://hdl.loc.gov/loc.music/ih